<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-23T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-23T13:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">125.6336/11–1348: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-23T13:00:00-05:00">November 23,
                                1948—1 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1683. Concur urtel 2199 Nov 13 and Shanghai 2388 Nov 11 pouched Nanking 1806
                        re Mukden proposal display Communist literature USIS library. Disapprove
                        USIS libraries displaying other Govt’s literature. Principle applies
                        worldwide regardless Govts involved. <pb facs="0850" n="840" xml:id="pg_840"/> Assume Emb answering Mukden’s 537 Nov 9 and 564 Nov 13 and transmitting
                        Dept views indicated above and in Deptel 1630 Nov 16.<note n="57" xml:id="d755fn57">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_573">p. 573</ref>.</note>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>